At the St Augustine Alligator Farm and #Zoological #Park, many birds come to nest and raise their young in the trees over the swamp filled with alligators. This kind of #mutualism sees the birds and their nests protected from other predators that might come from the ground, and alligators get them instead.
Many #birds #nest use this as a #rookery, like this #Tricolored #Heron, standing over her two #eggs.

content:
A new study found that #ocean warming has driven Antarctic sea ice into a permanently diminished state, with devastating implications for #ClimateChange.

2023 recorded a record low for ice coverage: 36% below the average summer minimum for 1979–2022. Less ice reflecting the sun means more exposed #water absorbing it, which accelerates the trend in a vicious feedback loop.

The Antarctic decline that #climate models predicted seems to be underway. Dire consequences loom for ecosystems, #weather, and #SeaLevelRise. Late last year, 10,000 emperor penguin chicks drowned when the ice broke beneath them before they grew waterproof feathers. How many of our own coastal communities must join them before Earth's leaders take action on the #ClimateCrisis?

Read a summary from the study's authors and link to their full report on Phys.org: https://is.gd/2aK98S
